    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Risk management</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Identifying, assessing, and mitigating risks to an org=
anization's assets and resources.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data-se=
arch=3D"risk mitigation  implementing controls and countermeasures to reduc=
e the potential impact or likelihood of security risks. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Risk mitigation</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Implementing controls and countermeasures to reduce th=
e potential impact or likelihood of security risks.</p></div><div class=3D"=
card term" data-search=3D"router  a networking device that forwards data pa=
ckets between networks based on ip addresses. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Router</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">A networking device that forwards data packets between=
 networks based on IP addresses.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data-sea=
rch=3D"secure configuration management  applying settings to network device=
s, servers, and applications to reduce vulnerabilities. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Secure configuration management=
</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Applying settings to network devices, servers, and app=
lications to reduce vulnerabilities.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data=
-search=3D"secure network segmentation  dividing a network into smaller sub=
networks to isolate sensitive systems and minimize the impact of a security=
 breach. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Secure network segmentation</sp=
an></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Dividing a network into smaller subnetworks to isolate=
 sensitive systems and minimize the impact of a security breach.</p></div><=
div class=3D"card term" data-search=3D"security auditing  evaluating the ef=
fectiveness of security controls and compliance with security policies and =
standards. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Security auditing</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Evaluating the effectiveness of security controls and =
compliance with security policies and standards.</p></div><div class=3D"car=
d term" data-search=3D"security awareness &amp; training  programs designed=
 to educate employees on security best practices, policies, and procedures =
and to promote a security-conscious culture. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Security awareness &amp; traini=
ng</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Programs designed to educate employees on security bes=
t practices, policies, and procedures and to promote a security-conscious c=
ulture.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data-search=3D"security ir  a doc=
umented process for detecting, responding to, and recovering from security =
incidents. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Security IR</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">A documented process for detecting, responding to, and=
 recovering from security incidents.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data=
-search=3D"security policy  a documented set of rules, guidelines, and proc=
edures that define an organization's approach to security. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Security policy</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">A documented set of rules, guidelines, and procedures =
that define an organization's approach to security.</p></div><div class=3D"=
card term" data-search=3D"security procedures  detailed step-by-step instru=
ctions for performing security-related tasks and actions consistently with =
security policies. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Security procedures</span></div=
>
    <p class=3D"def">Detailed step-by-step instructions for performing secu=
rity-related tasks and actions consistently with security policies.</p></di=
v><div class=3D"card term" data-search=3D"separation of duties  assigning d=
ifferent responsibilities to different individuals to prevent a single pers=
on from having complete control over a critical process or system. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Separation of duties</span></di=
v>
    <p class=3D"def">Assigning different responsibilities to different indi=
viduals to prevent a single person from having complete control over a crit=
ical process or system.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data-search=3D"so=
cial engineering  using psychological manipulation to trick people into div=
ulging confidential information or performing actions not in their best int=
erest. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Social engineering</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Using psychological manipulation to trick people into =
divulging confidential information or performing actions not in their best =
interest.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data-search=3D"software vulnera=
bilities  weaknesses or flaws in software code that attackers can exploit. =
">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Software vulnerabilities</span>=
</div>
    <p class=3D"def">Weaknesses or flaws in software code that attackers ca=
n exploit.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data-search=3D"spear phishing =
 targeted phishing attacks that appear personalized and trustworthy to dece=
ive specific individuals. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Spear phishing</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Targeted phishing attacks that appear personalized and=
 trustworthy to deceive specific individuals.</p></div><div class=3D"card t=
erm" data-search=3D"spyware  software that secretly collects information ab=
out a user's activities without their knowledge or consent. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Spyware</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Software that secretly collects information about a us=
er's activities without their knowledge or consent.</p></div><div class=3D"=
card term" data-search=3D"sql injection  exploiting vulnerabilities in web =
applications to manipulate or retrieve sensitive information from databases=
. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">SQL injection</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Exploiting vulnerabilities in web applications to mani=
pulate or retrieve sensitive information from databases.</p></div><div clas=
s=3D"card term" data-search=3D"stateful inspection firewalls  firewalls tha=
t track the state of network connections to allow or deny traffic based on =
