    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Stateful inspection firewalls</=
span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Firewalls that track the state of network connections =
to allow or deny traffic based on a connection's current state.</p></div><d=
iv class=3D"card term" data-search=3D"switch  a device that connects device=
s within a network and enables data transmission between them. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Switch</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">A device that connects devices within a network and en=
ables data transmission between them.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" dat=
a-search=3D"symmetric encryption  a cryptographic method (e.g., aes, 3des) =
that uses the same key for both encryption and decryption; efficient but re=
quires secure key distribution. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Symmetric encryption</span></di=
v>
    <p class=3D"def">A cryptographic method (e.g., AES, 3DES) that uses the=
 same key for both encryption and decryption; efficient but requires secure=
 key distribution.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data-search=3D"tailgat=
ing  gaining unauthorized physical access to a restricted area by following=
 an authorized person. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Tailgating</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Gaining unauthorized physical access to a restricted a=
rea by following an authorized person.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" da=
ta-search=3D"trojans  malicious programs disguised as legitimate software t=
hat can perform unauthorized actions. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Trojans</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Malicious programs disguised as legitimate software th=
at can perform unauthorized actions.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data=
-search=3D"user account management  creating, modifying, and deactivating u=
ser accounts, including assigning appropriate permissions and access rights=
. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">User account management</span><=
/div>
    <p class=3D"def">Creating, modifying, and deactivating user accounts, i=
ncluding assigning appropriate permissions and access rights.</p></div><div=
 class=3D"card term" data-search=3D"virtualization  creating virtual versio=
ns of computer hardware, operating systems, and applications. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Virtualization</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Creating virtual versions of computer hardware, operat=
ing systems, and applications.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data-searc=
h=3D"viruses  self-replicating programs that infect other files and can cau=
se damage. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Viruses</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Self-replicating programs that infect other files and =
can cause damage.</p></div><div class=3D"card term" data-search=3D"vulnerab=
ility  a weakness or flaw in a system or network that attackers can exploit=
. ">
    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Vulnerability</span></div>
