    <div class=3D"top"><span class=3D"term">Zoning</span></div>
    <p class=3D"def">Dividing a SAN into logical groups to control access a=
nd improve performance.</p></div></div>
  </section>

  <section data-block=3D"domain">
    <div class=3D"section-head"><h2>Exam Domains</h2><span class=3D"tag">Wh=
at's covered</span></div>
    <p class=3D"section-desc">The major knowledge areas these terms map to,=
 grouped the way the certification objectives organize them.</p>
    <div class=3D"dom-grid"><div class=3D"dom-card"><h3>Threats, Attacks &a=
mp; Vulnerabilities</h3><ul><li>Malware: adware, ransomware, spyware, Troja=
ns, viruses, worms</li><li>Attack methods &amp; vectors: brute force, DoS/D=
DoS, MitM, SQL injection, XSS, zero-day exploits</li><li>Social engineering=
: dumpster diving, impersonation, phishing, pretexting, spear phishing, tai=
lgating</li><li>Vulnerabilities &amp; their impact: configuration, hardware=
, human, and software vulnerabilities</li></ul></div><div class=3D"dom-card=
"><h3>Technologies &amp; Tools</h3><ul><li>Firewall technologies &amp; conf=
iguration: application, network, and stateful inspection firewalls</li><li>=
Encryption &amp; decryption: asymmetric, symmetric, and hashing</li><li>Net=
work topologies &amp; devices: AP, LAN, VPN, WAN, proxy server, router, swi=
tch</li><li>Security protocols: SSL, TLS, and AC technologies (AAA, MFA, RB=
AC); authentication and authorization</li></ul></div><div class=3D"dom-card=
"><h3>Architecture &amp; Design</h3><ul><li>Security controls: least privil=
ege, separation of duties</li><li>Designing secure networks: defense-in-dep=
th, secure configuration management, secure network segmentation</li><li>Id=
entifying &amp; mitigating risks: patch management, risk assessment, risk m=
itigation</li><li>Security assessment &amp; testing: penetration testing, s=
ecurity auditing, security IR, vulnerability assessment</li></ul></div><div=
 class=3D"dom-card"><h3>Identity &amp; Access Management</h3><ul><li>Managi=
ng &amp; securing user accounts: password hashing, policies, user account m=
anagement</li><li>Implementing MFA</li><li>Identity &amp; access management=
 technologies: Kerberos, LDAP</li></ul></div><div class=3D"dom-card"><h3>Ri=
sk Management</h3><ul><li>Risk management concepts: acceptance, analysis, a=
ssessment, mitigation</li><li>IR, IRP &amp; DRP: developing and implementin=
g security awareness &amp; training, policies, procedures</li></ul></div><d=
iv class=3D"dom-card"><h3>Cryptography &amp; PKI</h3><ul><li>Basic cryptogr=
aphic concepts: cryptography, asymmetric and symmetric encryption</li><li>U=
sing cryptography to protect data in transit and at rest</li><li>Understand=
ing PKI &amp; its components: PKI, DC, CA, certificate revocation, key pair=
</li></ul></div></div>
  </section>

